<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182190>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Mysmenopsis regi n. sp., male. A, habitus, dorsal. B, abdomen, posterior. C−E, left palp. C, retrolateral (arrow points to retrolateral cusps). D, prolateral. E, dorsal. Abbreviations, CG, cymbial groove. E, embolus. EA, embolic apophysis. P, pedicel. Pc, paracymbium. Scale bars, A, B, 0.3 mm. C-E, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182190/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8182192>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Mysmenopsis regiae n. sp., left male palp and right leg I, mirrored. A, retrolateral. B, prolateral. C, dorsal apical, filled embolus. D, leg I, tibia and metatarsus. Abbreviations, CG, cymbial groove. E, embolus. EA, embolic apophysis. Pc, paracymbium. Scale bars, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8182192/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

